# Shipping ≠ merging — at-hand reference

Full rule: `AGENTS.md` → *Shipping is not done when the PR is
merged*.

A merged-but-broken PR is a broken ship. After every merge:

1. **Wait for the PR's checks.** `gh pr checks <n>` (or
   `gh pr view <n> --json statusCheckRollup`) until all required
   checks finish. Auto-merge does not mean CI has passed.
2. **Verify the post-merge run** on `main`:
   `gh run list --branch main --limit 5`. Wait if
   `in_progress`.
3. **If red, YOU fix it — same session, new PR.** Even if the
   failure looks unrelated or flaky, treat it as yours until proven
   otherwise. Read logs with `gh run view <run-id> --log-failed`.
   Repeat until `main` is green.
4. **Never silence checks.** No `--no-verify`, no disabled
   workflows, no skipped tests to get green. Genuinely flaky tests
   are marked the way the project already handles flakes; surface
   the flake to the user.

If shipping multiple PRs, complete the watch-and-fix loop for PR N
before starting PR N+1.
